{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.36",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 36 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:1",
      "text": "Elihu also continued, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:2",
      "text": "“Bear with me a little, and I will show you; for I still have something to say on God’s behalf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:3",
      "text": "I will get my knowledge from afar, and will ascribe righteousness to my Maker.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:4",
      "text": "For truly my words are not false. One who is perfect in knowledge is with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:5",
      "text": "“ Behold, God is mighty, and doesn’t despise anyone. He is mighty in strength of understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:6",
      "text": "He doesn’t preserve the life of the wicked, but gives justice to the afflicted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:7",
      "text": "He doesn’t withdraw his eyes from the righteous, but with kings on the throne, he sets them forever, and they are exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:8",
      "text": "If they are bound in fetters, and are taken in the cords of afflictions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:9",
      "text": "then he shows them their work, and their transgressions, that they have behaved themselves proudly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:10",
      "text": "He also opens their ears to instruction, and commands that they return from iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:11",
      "text": "If they listen and serve him, they will spend their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:12",
      "text": "But if they don’t listen, they will perish by the sword; they will die without knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:13",
      "text": "“ But those who are godless in heart lay up anger. They don’t cry for help when he binds them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:14",
      "text": "They die in youth. Their life perishes among the unclean.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:15",
      "text": "He delivers the afflicted by their affliction, and opens their ear in oppression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:16",
      "text": "Yes, he would have allured you out of distress, into a wide place, where there is no restriction. That which is set on your table would be full of fatness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:17",
      "text": "“ But you are full of the judgment of the wicked. Judgment and justice take hold of you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:18",
      "text": "Don’t let riches entice you to wrath, neither let the great size of a bribe turn you aside.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:19",
      "text": "Would your wealth sustain you in distress, or all the might of your strength?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:20",
      "text": "Don’t desire the night, when people are cut off in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:21",
      "text": "Take heed, don’t regard iniquity; for you have chosen this rather than affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:22",
      "text": "Behold, God is exalted in his power. Who is a teacher like him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:23",
      "text": "Who has prescribed his way for him? Or who can say, ‘ You have committed unrighteousness ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:24",
      "text": "“ Remember that you magnify his work, about which men have sung.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:25",
      "text": "All men have looked on it. Man sees it afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:26",
      "text": "Behold, God is great, and we don’t know him. The number of his years is unsearchable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:27",
      "text": "For he draws up the drops of water, which distill in rain from his vapor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:28",
      "text": "which the skies pour down and which drop on man abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:29",
      "text": "Indeed, can anyone understand the spreading of the clouds and the thunderings of his pavilion?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:30",
      "text": "Behold, he spreads his light around him. He covers the bottom of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:31",
      "text": "For by these he judges the people. He gives food in abundance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:32",
      "text": "He covers his hands with the lightning, and commands it to strike the mark.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.36.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:33",
      "text": "Its noise tells about him, and the livestock also, concerning the storm that comes up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
